step 1: Build Linux server ( rocky or redhat or centOS)
step 2: install ansible package in Linux server
step 3: install git package in Linux srever
step 4: install gitbash in your laptop
step 5: Install VSCode in your laptop
step 5: open your D drive and create one folder like Ansible-Learning
step 6: open VS code and open your Ansibel-Learning folder in VScode
	Click on file--click on open folder--select your created folder in latop
step 7: open gitbash and run cd /D/Ansible-Learning/
step 8: open GitHub in browser create the new account. And if already exists then create one repo like Ansible
step 9: open gitbash clone your repo 
		git clone https://github.com/bhimisetty-devops/
		ls
		cd Ansible
Step 10: open VSCode and start code then open gitbash and run git add .; git commit -m "new file added"; git push origin main. (push code to GitHub)
Step 11: Create remote servers ex: Remote-1 and Remote-2
Step 12: Add remote servers IP's in Ansible inventory file
Step 13: Create separate "ansible" user in all 3 servers ( Ansible and remote node's)
Step 14: switch to anisble user in ansible server
Step 15: Now generate keys (Private and Public) in ansible server using below command.
Step 16: Copy public key to remote nodes for passwordless authenticating 
        $ ssh-copy-id ansible@192.168.30.136
        $ ssh-copy-id ansible@192.168.30.149
    Note: Now we can able to see authorized_keys in remote servers on below location
            /home/ansible/.ssh
            authorized_keys
Step 17: Check passwordless authentication success or not using below command from ansible server
        $ ssh 192.168.30.149
step 18: open Linux Ansible server and clone the gitbash repo and pull the code and run in server
		git clone https://github.com/bhimisetty-devops/Ansible

